OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 28 Jul to Thu 6 AugFA
OL,6,Fchangeable period is likely to start,
OL,7,Fwith many areas seeing a mixture of
OL,8,Fbright or sunny spells and some rain
OL,9,Fat times. Northwestern areas are more
OL,10,Flikely to see the focus of rainfall,
OL,11,Fbut elsewhere outbreaks of showers or
OL,12,Fthunderstorms may interrupt the dry
OL,13,Fconditions at times elsewhere.
OL,14,FConfidence becomes lower into the
OL,15,Fstart of August, but there are hints
OL,16,Fthat more settled conditions could
OL,17,Freturn for a time, which would mean
OL,18,Fdry conditions resuming, especially in
OL,19,Fthe south. Winds will be mostly light
OL,20,For moderate, but occasionally fresh or
OL,21,Fstrong around some coasts, mainly in
OL,22,Fthe north and west. Temperatures will
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fbe broadly above normal and will
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fprobably be warm or even hot at times
OL,25,Fin the south.
